<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Determining components of a resultant vector and it's magnitude</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>In a 2D coordinate system, vector <b>a</b> point from the origin to <b>A({@ax@}, {@ay@})</b> and vector <b>b</b> point from the origin to <b>B({@bx@}, {@by@})</b>.</p>

[[jsxgraph width="400px" height="400px"]]
var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {
    boundingbox: [-1, 12, 12, -1], 
    axis: true, 
    showCopyright: false
});

var origin = board.create('point', [0, 0], {name: 'O', size: 2, fixed: true, color: 'black'});
var pA = board.create('point', [{#ax#}, {#ay#}], {name: 'A', size: 3, fixed: true});
var pB = board.create('point', [{#bx#}, {#by#}], {name: 'B', size: 3, fixed: true});

var vecA = board.create('arrow', [origin, pA], {strokeColor: 'blue', name: 'a', withLabel: true});
var vecB = board.create('arrow', [origin, pB], {strokeColor: 'red', name: 'b', withLabel: true});

// The subtraction vector (a - b) points from the tip of b to the tip of a
board.create('arrow', [pB, pA], {strokeColor: 'green', dash: 2, withLabel: true});
[[/jsxgraph]]


<p>Determine the components of the resultant vector \(\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}\).</p>
<ol>
    <li>\(\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}\) =  [[input:ans1]] \(, \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
    <li>
<p>Calculate the magnitude of the resultant vector above.</p>
<p>\(|\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}| = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p>
</li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<b> 1: Determine the Resultant Components </b>
<p>To find \(\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}\), we subtract the corresponding components of vector \(\mathbf{b}\) from vector \(\mathbf{a}\):</p>
\(\begin{align}
\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} &= (x_a - x_b, y_a - y_b) \\
&= ({@ax@} - {@bx@}, {@ay@} - {@by@}) \\
&= \mathbf{({@ta1@}, {@ta2@})}
\end{align}\)

<b>2: Calculate the Magnitude</b>
<p>The magnitude is the geometric length of the resulting vector (the dashed green line in the graph):</p>
\(\begin{align}
|\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}| &= \sqrt{x_{\text{comp}}^2 + y_{\text{comp}}^2} \\
&= \sqrt{({@ta1@})^2 + ({@ta2@})^2} \\
&= \sqrt{{@mag_sq@}} \\
&= \mathbf{{@ta3@}}
\end{align}\)]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
